#Text=Poland : Thousands of far-right nationalists gather in Warsaw to march for white supremacy , anti-liberalism , and anti-Islam on Polish independence day
#Text=Tuesday , November 14 , 2017

#Text=On Saturday afternoon , thousands of far-right nationalists gathered in Poland 's capital Warsaw to participate in " Independence March " which was organized by far-right groups including All-Polish Youth , the National Movement , and the National-Radical Camp .

column1: #Text=Participants objected to liberalism , Islam , and some banners supported white supremacy .
#Text=The slogan of this year 's Independence March was " We want god " .
#Text=The march , which coincided with Poland 's independence day , began at 3:00 P.M. local time ( 1400 UTC ) .

#Text=Marchers chanted " Great national Poland , religion is the basis of the Polish nation , Great Catholic Poland and one nation across the borders " under banners reading " We want God " and " White Europe of brotherly nations . "

column1: #Text=There were also anti-leftist , anti- United States slogans as well as slogans against liberal media broadcasters .
#Text=Poland 's Interior Minister Mariusz Błaszczak said , " We are proud that so many Poles have decided to take part in a celebration connected to the Independence Day holiday . "
#Text=Andrzej Duda , Polish president , condemned the march and called this march a display of " sick nationalism " .
#Text=He also added " there is no place [ for xenophobia ] in Poland " .

#Text=Emmanuel Nahshon , spokesperson of the Israeli Foreign Ministry , called the march " a dangerous march of extreme and racist elements " and told the Associated Press , " We hope that Polish authorities will act against the organisers [ ... ]

#Text=Only one clash between the two groups was reported , of a man kicking women who were holding a flag reading  Stop Fascism . "

column1: #Text=The event drew people from other European countries , including Slovakia , Sweden and Hungary .
#Text=39-year-old Richard Spencer , a white supremacist from the United States , was invited to Poland by far-right groups , and he was scheduled to attend the event but did not .
#Text=On October 27 , Poland 's Foreign Minister Witold Waszczykowski said , " He [ Spencer ] should not appear publicly , and especially not in Poland . "

#Text=Saying Spencer 's opinions " are in conflict with the legal order " of the country , Waszczykowski added , " as a country which was one of the biggest victims of Nazism , we believe that the ideas promoted by Mr Spencer and his followers could pose a threat to all those who hold dear the values of human rights and democracy " .
#Text=November 11 is the anniversary of the end of World War I , after which Poland regained its status as an independent country in 1918 .
#Text=The Independence March was first organised in 2009 and the number of participants has grown since .
